871
00:50:49.424 --> 00:50:52.684
But before I show you data, I would like to introduce what is a ketogenic diet.

872
00:50:52.864 --> 00:50:56.444
A ketogenic diet is a diet that is high in fat and low in carbohydrate.

873
00:50:56.544 --> 00:50:57.944
It's different than high fat diet.

874
00:50:57.964 --> 00:51:01.744
A ketogenic diet has to push body through the state of ketosis.

875
00:51:01.784 --> 00:51:05.744
A state of ketosis is a process of using fatty acid to producing

876
00:51:05.764 --> 00:51:08.294
ketone bodies. But what does it mean for tumors?

877
00:51:09.104 --> 00:51:12.913
For tumors, pretty much it means that under an average Western diet, tumor is

878
00:51:12.944 --> 00:51:15.724
capable to pick up nutrient in a form of carbohydrate,

879
00:51:16.804 --> 00:51:20.664
make glucose, and use that glucose to push through glycolysis,

880
00:51:20.764 --> 00:51:22.944
TCA cycle, and other macromolecules to grow.

881
00:51:23.524 --> 00:51:27.264
However, under a ketogenic diet, tumor has to rely on ketone

882
00:51:27.304 --> 00:51:30.744
bodies, and ketone bodies are made in liver from fatty acids.

883
00:51:31.284 --> 00:51:34.124
So from the beginning, we have a diet that will

884
00:51:34.924 --> 00:51:38.284
inhibit glycolysis to not produce enough nutrient for

885
00:51:38.344 --> 00:51:42.224
glycolysis, and these tumors have to use their TCA cycle

886
00:51:42.284 --> 00:51:45.764
as a major source of nutrient production and energy production.

887
00:51:48.124 --> 00:51:52.024
In the field to date, we have multiple studies that have been published on

888
00:51:52.044 --> 00:51:55.624
the effect of ketogenic diet in combination therapy with other

889
00:51:55.684 --> 00:51:57.824
therapeutics. I have three of them here.

890
00:51:57.944 --> 00:51:59.764
The first study is from the laboratory of Dr.

891
00:52:00.024 --> 00:52:03.624
Cantley, where they showed that ketogenic diet in combination with PI3K

892
00:52:03.664 --> 00:52:06.304
inhibitor shows a stronger anticancer effect.

893
00:52:06.344 --> 00:52:10.024
And the reason for it is that ketogenic diet has lower amount of carbohydrate.

894
00:52:10.164 --> 00:52:14.004
We have lower amount of insulin, so PI3K inhibitors would be more efficient.

895
00:52:14.724 --> 00:52:16.594
The second study from the laboratory of Dr.

896
00:52:17.104 --> 00:52:20.324
Vander Heiden suggests that ketogenic diet alone does not have much of an

897
00:52:20.364 --> 00:52:24.193
effect. However, if we change the source of fatty acid and

898
00:52:24.264 --> 00:52:28.004
make them more saturated, we might be able to get some anticancer

899
00:52:28.084 --> 00:52:31.984
efficacy from ketogenic diet. And the third study from the laboratory

900
00:52:32.024 --> 00:52:36.004
of Dr. Ruggiero from UCSF shows that the effectiveness

901
00:52:36.024 --> 00:52:39.884
of ketogenic diet comes in inhibition and combination therapy with inhibitor

902
00:52:39.944 --> 00:52:42.244
of ketone body utilization genes.

903
00:52:42.984 --> 00:52:46.144
What you can see in common between all three studies, and all the studies in the

904
00:52:46.184 --> 00:52:50.054
field, is that all the studies suggest that ketogenic diet alone is

905
00:52:50.064 --> 00:52:53.864
not going to be effective. And all of these three studies that I showed here, it

906
00:52:53.904 --> 00:52:57.464
shows that there are different angles that ketogenic diet in a

907
00:52:57.504 --> 00:52:59.024
combination therapy can be effective.

908
00:52:59.184 --> 00:53:03.084
So there is a lot more to discover. And what we have studied is that

909
00:53:03.104 --> 00:53:06.484
every time that we administered ketogenic diet, we saw that the tumor

910
00:53:06.544 --> 00:53:10.304
progression was slower, survival was longer, but even

911
00:53:10.344 --> 00:53:14.034
after 227 days, we still have tumor in the mice,

912
00:53:14.344 --> 00:53:15.564
but they're just growing slower.

913
00:53:16.544 --> 00:53:19.984
So we ask a question that how does a ketogenic diet cause adaptation?

914
00:53:20.084 --> 00:53:23.054
What are the adaptation pathway that arises from ketogenic diet?

915
00:53:23.924 --> 00:53:27.824
For the first step, we did a series of metabolomics, and we saw that

916
00:53:27.884 --> 00:53:31.824
a cell line like MiaPaCa that historically has been established to be glycolytic,

917
00:53:32.484 --> 00:53:36.044
under ketogenic diet condition, their tumors become

918
00:53:36.104 --> 00:53:39.424
TCA cycle dependent. They upregulate TCA cycle activity.

919
00:53:39.444 --> 00:53:41.804
They have more metabolites in their TCA cycle.

920
00:53:42.964 --> 00:53:46.804
We also saw that when we administered ketogenic diet in the serum, we have a lot of

921
00:53:46.844 --> 00:53:50.744
fatty acid upregulation. However, in the tumor, selected few of those fatty

922
00:53:50.804 --> 00:53:54.604
acids are upregulated. And finally, by accident, which

