950
00:55:31.744 --> 00:55:34.784
ketogenic diet conditions are upregulated.

951
00:55:34.884 --> 00:55:35.984
We have more channels to

952
00:55:37.124 --> 00:55:40.754
pick up more glutamine, and we have more enzyme that utilize glutamine.

953
00:55:40.774 --> 00:55:43.744
So at this point, we know that the glutamine levels are higher.

954
00:55:44.104 --> 00:55:47.883
We know that the ability of the tumor to pick up glutamine is higher, and they do

955
00:55:47.944 --> 00:55:51.894
have the machinery to utilize it. Next, we did a series of isotope tracing with

956
00:55:51.904 --> 00:55:55.324
glutamine, and we saw that, yes, pancreatic cancer, not only they are capable to

957
00:55:55.364 --> 00:55:59.224
pick up the glutamine, they're actually capable of utilizing this glutamine

958
00:55:59.244 --> 00:56:00.444
to feed their TCA cycle.

959
00:56:02.024 --> 00:56:05.544
All of this data so far shows that we have more glutamine in the tumor,

960
00:56:06.204 --> 00:56:10.084
but we cannot say that tumors are dependent on glutamine.

961
00:56:10.684 --> 00:56:14.664
We can only suggest that tumors are dependent on glutamine if we show that the flux

962
00:56:14.744 --> 00:56:18.724
of glutamine is faster and the glutamine is being utilized

963
00:56:18.784 --> 00:56:22.624
faster in the tumor. So to show that the flux is faster and

964
00:56:22.704 --> 00:56:26.434
utilization is higher, we did a series of isotope tracing, this

965
00:56:26.504 --> 00:56:30.404
time, time-based. We looked at the utilization of glutamine

966
00:56:30.524 --> 00:56:33.024
at half an hour, one hour, two hour, and three hour.

967
00:56:33.164 --> 00:56:36.754
We saw that at half an hour, when we remove all the glutamine from the media and

968
00:56:36.784 --> 00:56:39.834
replace it with M5 glutamine, isotope tracer of glutamine,

969
00:56:40.764 --> 00:56:44.084
right off the bat, we have more glutamine in the ketogenic diet condition.

970
00:56:44.164 --> 00:56:45.944
We saw it in the tumor, we see it in the cell culture.

971
00:56:46.584 --> 00:56:50.304
After three hours, the amount of glutamine in both condition, ketogenic

972
00:56:50.364 --> 00:56:53.184
diet and control diet, reached to be the same amount.

973
00:56:53.964 --> 00:56:57.444
When we start at the higher levels and reach the same amount, it means that the

974
00:56:57.484 --> 00:57:00.404
velocity and utilization was faster. We push it further.

975
00:57:00.544 --> 00:57:04.144
We look into the glutamate. We look into alpha-KG and aspartate

976
00:57:04.464 --> 00:57:08.084
at M3. We wanted to see if M5 is also being utilized faster.

977
