pancreatic cancer fibrosis.

1075
01:02:05.004 --> 01:02:06.464
I don't have anything to disclose.

1076
01:02:08.004 --> 01:02:11.884
Pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma, or PDAC, is the third leading cause of

1077
01:02:11.924 --> 01:02:15.524
cancer-related death in the United States, with only

1078
01:02:15.544 --> 01:02:18.664
13% of patients living beyond five years.

1079
01:02:19.564 --> 01:02:23.544
The dismal prognosis of this disease is because of its highly metastatic

1080
01:02:23.604 --> 01:02:27.294
nature and its refractoriness to standard cytotoxic and

1081
01:02:27.384 --> 01:02:28.204
immune therapy.

1082
01:02:29.804 --> 01:02:33.684
The treatment unresponsiveness of this disease is

1083
01:02:34.104 --> 01:02:36.984
largely because of its unique fibrotic and

1084
01:02:37.784 --> 01:02:41.404
stroma-rich microenvironment, where cancer-associated fibroblasts

1085
01:02:41.484 --> 01:02:44.704
become one of the major cell types, as can be seen in this

1086
01:02:45.144 --> 01:02:48.964
multiplex IHC image where yellow and red

1087
01:02:49.044 --> 01:02:52.684
marks total CAF as well as a subtype of

1088
01:02:52.764 --> 01:02:55.064
CAF in PDAC tumor microenvironment.

1089
01:02:57.084 --> 01:03:00.764
Cancer-associated fibroblasts, or CAF, play a crucial role in

1090
01:03:00.884 --> 01:03:01.284
TME.

1091
01:03:02.344 --> 01:03:06.284
It deposits extracellular matrix as well as it can remodel extracellular matrix.

1092
01:03:06.784 --> 01:03:10.274
It can regulate antitumor immune responses and can

1093
01:03:10.324 --> 01:03:14.104
fuel energetics as well as proliferation of tumor cells.

1094
01:03:14.784 --> 01:03:18.144
However, in PDAC, studies that have targeted

1095
01:03:18.724 --> 01:03:22.444
CAF has shown both pro and antitumorigenic outcome.

1096
01:03:23.424 --> 01:03:27.014
And the reason behind this can be found in the phenotypic and

1097
01:03:27.124 --> 01:03:30.593
functional heterogeneity of CAF in the tumor microenvironment.

1098
01:03:31.644 --> 01:03:35.424
In PDAC, three subpopulation of CAFs are well known,

1099
01:03:35.984 --> 01:03:39.604
which are inflammatory CAF, antigen-presenting CAF, and

1100
01:03:39.664 --> 01:03:43.533
myofibroblastic CAF. Moreover, there are other subpopulation

1101
01:03:43.533 --> 01:03:47.364
of CAFs that has been identified with particular markers such

1102
01:03:47.404 --> 01:03:50.804
as LRRC15, CD105, and FAP.

1103
01:03:51.804 --> 01:03:55.184
Adding to this heterogeneity, our recent work has

1104
01:03:55.244 --> 01:03:59.064
identified a subpopulation of myofibroblasts that has

1105
01:03:59.124 --> 01:04:02.504
undergone senescence and regulate PDAC progression.

1106
01:04:04.764 --> 01:04:08.244
Under the presence of external and internal stress, such as

1107
01:04:08.304 --> 01:04:11.884
genotoxic stress, oncogene activation, and telomere erosion,

1108
01:04:12.344 --> 01:04:16.244
cell activate signaling cascade leading to upregulation of cell

1109
01:04:16.324 --> 01:04:19.514
cycle inhibitor such as P16 and P21,

1110
01:04:20.124 --> 01:04:22.824
which leads to irreversible arrest in cell cycle.

1111
01:04:23.484 --> 01:04:26.794
Along with this, there are several cell autonomous and

1112
01:04:26.844 --> 01:04:30.204
non-autonomous events occur, such as chromatin

1113
01:04:30.264 --> 01:04:33.824
rearrangement, metabolic reprogramming, and these cells secrete a

1114
01:04:33.864 --> 01:04:37.544
plethora of signaling and matrix remodeling protein, which are

1115
01:04:37.584 --> 01:04:40.694
collectively known as senescence-associated secretory phenotype.

1116
01:04:41.984 --> 01:04:45.784
So we identified a subset of CAF, particularly

1117
01:04:45.824 --> 01:04:48.724
myofibroblasts, that have undergone senescence,

1118
01:04:49.464 --> 01:04:53.384
as can be seen in this multiplex IHC images where the

1119
01:04:53.444 --> 01:04:57.264
top panel are tumor from genetic mouse model of PDAC, which is

1120
01:04:57.344 --> 01:05:01.304
KP-PC, and the bottom panel is a human PDAC

1121
01:05:01.364 --> 01:05:04.104
sample. And you can see these green

1122
01:05:04.684 --> 01:05:08.664
P16-expressing senescent cells, and you can appreciate that these

1123
01:05:08.704 --> 01:05:12.004
cells are particularly restricted to these alpha-SMA expressing

1124
01:05:12.024 --> 01:05:15.664
myofibroblasts, suggesting these senescent cells are just a

1125
01:05:15.704 --> 01:05:17.464
subpopulation of myofibroblasts.

1126
01:05:18.984 --> 01:05:19.444
Moreover,

1127
01:05:20.484 --> 01:05:24.244
when we orthotopically co-implanted senescent fibroblasts with

1128
01:05:24.324 --> 01:05:26.104
PDAC cell line,

1129
01:05:26.984 --> 01:05:30.464
it led to more tumor burden as compared to implantation of

1130
01:05:30.504 --> 01:05:33.784
non-senescent fibroblasts with PDAC cell line,

1131
01:05:34.124 --> 01:05:37.664
suggesting senescent fibroblasts promote PDAC progression.

1132
01:05:39.024 --> 01:05:42.924
To ask what senescent fibroblasts are doing in PDAC

1133
01:05:42.934 --> 01:05:46.864
tumor microenvironment, we utilized this genetic mouse model called

1134
01:05:46.964 --> 01:05:50.844
Ink-Tag, and we combined this mouse with our

1135
01:05:51.084 --> 01:05:53.664
genetic mouse model of PDAC, which is KP-PC.

1136
01:05:54.664 --> 01:05:58.484
And depletion of senescent cells in this model led to

1137
01:05:58.524 --> 01:06:01.564
less collagen abundance in PDAC tumor

1138
01:06:01.824 --> 01:06:05.744
microenvironment, which was evaluated using Sirius red staining

1139
01:06:05.784 --> 01:06:09.674
and can be seen in this representative image as well as in

1140
01:06:09.704 --> 01:06:11.124
the quantification.

1141
01:06:12.174 --> 01:06:15.884
Moreover, we found that the collagen one

1142
01:06:15.964 --> 01:06:19.944
matrix deposited by senescent fibroblasts have

1143
01:06:20.104 --> 01:06:23.513
thicker fiber as compared to a matrix deposited by

1144
01:06:23.624 --> 01:06:24.874
non-senescent fibroblasts.

1145
01:06:25.884 --> 01:06:29.184
So we asked how senescent fibroblasts promote

1146
01:06:29.224 --> 01:06:32.524
fibrosis in PDAC tumor microenvironment, and our

1147
01:06:32.564 --> 01:06:36.384
hypothesis is metabolic reprogramming in

1148
01:06:36.424 --> 01:06:40.013
senescent CAF promote a fibrotic microenvironment in

1149
01:06:40.024 --> 01:06:40.544
PDAC.

1150
01:06:41.744 --> 01:06:43.924
To test this hypothesis, first,

1151
01:06:44.924 --> 01:06:47.984
we tested whether senescent

1152
01:06:48.144 --> 01:06:52.084
CAF are metabolically distinct as compared to myofibroblasts.

1153
01:06:52.584 --> 01:06:55.864
Towards this, we utilized single-cell RNA sequencing

1154
01:06:55.944 --> 01:06:59.884
library generated from sorted CAF from tumor

1155
01:07:00.064 --> 01:07:02.464
isolated from genetic mouse model of PDAC.

1156
01:07:03.184 --> 01:07:07.164
And dimensional reduction analysis demonstrated this presence of

1157
01:07:07.244 --> 01:07:10.384
purple cluster, which shows transcriptional signature of

1158
01:07:10.444 --> 01:07:14.172
senescence.Gene set enrichment analysis

1159
01:07:14.592 --> 01:07:17.712
demonstrated transcriptional enrichment of oxidative

1160
01:07:17.772 --> 01:07:21.412
phosphorylation and glycolysis in senescent CAF.

1161
01:07:22.292 --> 01:07:25.492
Since mitochondria are the hub of oxidative phosphorylation,

1162
01:07:25.972 --> 01:07:29.532
next we asked whether mitochondrial abundance and mitochondrial

1163
01:07:29.572 --> 01:07:32.342
function is altered in senescent fibroblasts.

1164
01:07:33.292 --> 01:07:36.782
To verse this, we induced senescence in primary pancreatic

1165
01:07:36.852 --> 01:07:39.812
fibroblasts using a DNA-damaging agent, bleomycin,

1166
01:07:40.692 --> 01:07:44.402
and assessed the mitochondrial content using MitoTracker and

1167
01:07:44.452 --> 01:07:47.992
mitochondrial potential using a TMRM dye.

1168
01:07:48.772 --> 01:07:52.652
And as can be seen here, although the induction of senescence led to

1169
01:07:52.712 --> 01:07:56.292
more mitochondrial content, the mitochondrial potential per

1170
01:07:56.332 --> 01:07:59.572
mitochondria is dampened in senescent fibroblasts,

1171
01:07:59.972 --> 01:08:03.712
suggesting potential impairment in mitochondrial function.

1172
01:08:04.732 --> 01:08:08.712
Moreover, to get a holistic overview of metabolic changes

1173
01:08:08.752 --> 01:08:12.652
associated with senescence, we performed untargeted metabolomics

1174
01:08:13.272 --> 01:08:16.432
and metabolite set enrichment analysis demonstrated

1175
01:08:17.052 --> 01:08:20.333
upregulation of glycolysis in senescent fibroblasts.

1176
01:08:21.753 --> 01:08:25.572
When we zoom in, we see enrichment of several glycolytic

1177
01:08:25.632 --> 01:08:27.713
intermediates in senescent fibroblasts.

1178
01:08:28.392 --> 01:08:32.152
However, interestingly, in TCA cycle, although the initial

1179
01:08:32.213 --> 01:08:35.932
metabolites such as citric acid and alpha-ketoglutaric acid is

1180
01:08:35.992 --> 01:08:39.753
enriched in senescent fibroblasts, the later metabolites like

1181
01:08:39.772 --> 01:08:42.352
succinate and malic acid are dampened.

1182
01:08:43.373 --> 01:08:44.952
I found this accumulation of

1183
01:08:44.992 --> 01:08:48.572
alpha-ketoglutarate in senescent fibroblasts

1184
01:08:48.592 --> 01:08:52.172
particularly interesting, since for the proper

1185
01:08:52.232 --> 01:08:56.072
folding as well as triplex formation of collagen, it

1186
01:08:56.132 --> 01:08:59.452
need to undergo proline and lysine hydroxylation.

1187
01:08:59.972 --> 01:09:02.772
And the enzymes which are involved in this process, such as

1188
01:09:03.913 --> 01:09:07.632
lysyl as well as prolyl hydroxylase, utilize

1189
01:09:07.692 --> 01:09:09.852
alpha-ketoglutarate as a substrate.

1190
01:09:10.932 --> 01:09:14.552
Supporting this, we found that senescent CAF

1191
01:09:14.732 --> 01:09:18.552
showed transcriptional upregulation of several prolyl as well as

1192
01:09:18.592 --> 01:09:20.172
lysyl hydroxylases.

1193
01:09:21.312 --> 01:09:24.692
Moreover, coming back to the accumulation of

1194
01:09:24.732 --> 01:09:28.572
alpha-ketoglutarate in senescent fibroblasts, we

1195
01:09:28.652 --> 01:09:32.512
found that the enzymes which are involved in

1196
01:09:32.873 --> 01:09:36.532
alpha-ketoglutarate production, which are IDH2 and

1197
01:09:36.632 --> 01:09:39.812
IDH3, are upregulated in senescent CAF.

1198
01:09:40.333 --> 01:09:44.232
Particularly, it was interesting because IDH2 and IDH3 are involved

1199
01:09:44.293 --> 01:09:48.152
in mitochondrial alpha-ketoglutarate production, although the IDH1 is

1200
01:09:48.192 --> 01:09:49.932
involved in cytosolic.

1201
01:09:51.652 --> 01:09:55.532
So the ongoing work is targeting IDH2

1202
01:09:55.572 --> 01:09:59.452
and IDH3 in senescent CAF and assessing its

1203
01:09:59.492 --> 01:10:03.092
effect on ECM production by senescent

1204
01:10:03.212 --> 01:10:03.572
CAF.

