1221
01:11:07.112 --> 01:11:08.872
mechanism is that because

1222
01:11:09.712 --> 01:11:13.612
for senescence induction, DNA damage is one of the common

1223
01:11:14.832 --> 01:11:18.792
event which occur, and lot of enzymes, particularly PARP,

1224
01:11:18.892 --> 01:11:20.532
which is a NAD-dependent

1225
01:11:21.332 --> 01:11:24.792
enzyme, deplete NAD, which leads to mitochondrial dysfunction.

1226
01:11:25.752 --> 01:11:26.272
Interesting.

1227
01:11:27.512 --> 01:11:31.472
And I guess one follow-up. It's sort of interesting to think about activating

1228
01:11:31.512 --> 01:11:35.312
a collagen biosynthesis program, but depleting AKG at the

1229
01:11:35.372 --> 01:11:39.312
same time. Have you tried to intervene and block AKG

1230
01:11:39.452 --> 01:11:42.062
supply to collagen-modifying enzymes?

1231
01:11:42.542 --> 01:11:46.432
And if so, does that lead to any proteostasis-related stress

1232
01:11:46.532 --> 01:11:47.152
or

1233
01:11:48.212 --> 01:11:51.452
toxic accumulation of procollagens within those cells?

1234
01:11:51.912 --> 01:11:55.292
Yeah. So those are exactly the experiments we are

1235
01:11:55.892 --> 01:11:59.472
doing to see, trying to see whether if we

1236
01:11:59.752 --> 01:12:03.692
inhibit this pathway, whether that can affect the

1237
01:12:03.732 --> 01:12:05.032
whole collagen production.

1238
01:12:05.412 --> 01:12:05.582
Mm-hmm.

1239
01:12:06.092 --> 01:12:09.772
Mostly ex vivo currently, but later want to go to in vivo.

1240
01:12:10.172 --> 01:12:10.472
Mm-hmm.

1241
01:12:11.672 --> 01:12:11.932
All right.

1242
01:12:12.512 --> 01:12:13.412
I have a question.

1243
01:12:15.552 --> 01:12:17.892
So you mentioned that there is an increase

1244
01:12:18.852 --> 01:12:22.552
in the alpha-ketoglutaric acid. Do you know if this acid

1245
01:12:22.572 --> 01:12:26.452
is accumulated in the fibroblasts or is released

1246
01:12:26.492 --> 01:12:27.652
to the microenvironment?

1247
01:12:28.732 --> 01:12:30.912
Yes. So we have also done

1248
01:12:31.392 --> 01:12:34.492
metabolomics on the condition media.

1249
01:12:35.192 --> 01:12:38.932
And as much I remember, the citric acid was high, but

1250
01:12:38.952 --> 01:12:42.432
alpha-ketoglutaric acid was not high in the condition media.

1251
01:12:42.972 --> 01:12:44.512
So yeah.

1252
01:12:44.572 --> 01:12:46.432
All right. That's what we wanted.

1253
01:12:46.442 --> 01:12:46.442
Yeah.

1254
01:12:46.492 --> 01:12:46.952
Thank you.

1255
01:12:47.012 --> 01:12:48.312
Yeah. Thank you.

1256
01:12:53.332 --> 01:12:56.332
Okay. Our next speaker is Dr. Alvaro Gutierrez.

1257
01:12:57.252 --> 01:13:00.412
He's a member of David Sodransky's lab, Johns Hopkins

1258
01:13:00.492 --> 01:13:01.252
University.

1259
01:13:02.152 --> 01:13:05.772
I'm not sure if I've seen Dr. Gutierrez.

1260
01:13:10.912 --> 01:13:11.512
He might be on

1261
01:13:11.552 --> 01:13:18.604
MiRAOkay.

1262
01:13:19.364 --> 01:13:22.704
I take that back. Our next speaker is Dr. Myra Di Tano.

1263
01:13:23.304 --> 01:13:26.984
She's a postdoctoral fellow in Marcos Goncalves's lab

1264
01:13:27.304 --> 01:13:31.174
at NYU. The title of her talk is Targeting

1265
01:13:31.244 --> 01:13:33.404
Metabolism in BRCA Deficient Tumors.

1266
01:13:34.084 --> 01:13:35.304
Thanks for your flexibility.

1267
01:13:35.694 --> 01:13:39.664
Of course. Thank you for the introduction and this opportunity.

1268
01:13:41.384 --> 01:13:41.664
Okay.

1269
01:13:43.544 --> 01:13:47.024
So I'm happy to share with you our data regarding

1270
01:13:47.064 --> 01:13:49.324
metabolism in BRCA deficient tumors.

1271
01:13:51.424 --> 01:13:52.384
So BRCA genes

1272
01:13:53.244 --> 01:13:56.604
are tumor suppressor genes, and they are key players in

1273
01:13:56.964 --> 01:14:00.264
homologous recombination gene repair pathway, which is an

1274
01:14:00.274 --> 01:14:04.224
error-free gene repair mechanism that fuels their survival

1275
01:14:04.264 --> 01:14:08.054
and maintains genome integrity. When BRCA genes get mutated,

1276
01:14:08.204 --> 01:14:11.784
homologous recombination gets impaired, and so the cells

1277
01:14:12.124 --> 01:14:16.064
need to use other alternative pathways which are usually error prone to

1278
01:14:16.104 --> 01:14:19.904
repair their DNA damage, and this fuels genomic instability, cell

1279
01:14:19.964 --> 01:14:21.464
death, and can lead to cancer.

1280
01:14:23.384 --> 01:14:27.324
And this is the reason why individuals with germline mutation in one of the copies

1281
01:14:27.364 --> 01:14:31.024
of these genes showed increased susceptibility to develop

1282
01:14:31.064 --> 01:14:31.904
different tumors.

1283
01:14:33.264 --> 01:14:37.104
So the main question, the main goal of this project is to understand whether and

1284
01:14:37.224 --> 01:14:40.524
how loss of BRCA genes may affect tumor metabolism.

1285
01:14:41.364 --> 01:14:43.864
And to answer these complicated questions, we

1286
01:14:45.064 --> 01:14:48.724
started with a simple in vitro system, which is the LD1 cell line,

1287
01:14:49.484 --> 01:14:52.904
which are isogenic cell line, BRCA2 wild type and BRCA2 knockout.

1288
01:14:53.344 --> 01:14:57.164
We interrogated them through RNA-Seq, and we could see

1289
01:14:57.204 --> 01:15:01.104
that among the top 10 hits, glycolysis/gluconeogenesis was

1290
01:15:01.114 --> 01:15:04.944
altered. And then we decided to look at the different protein

1291
01:15:04.984 --> 01:15:08.924
expression level of the different enzymes of glycolysis to see whether

1292
01:15:08.944 --> 01:15:12.484
they were altered. And we found that that was the case, and in

1293
01:15:12.524 --> 01:15:16.304
particular, we found an upregulation of pyruvate kinase upon

1294
01:15:16.344 --> 01:15:20.064
loss of BRCA2. So pyruvate kinase is the

1295
01:15:20.124 --> 01:15:24.064
enzyme which catalyzes the last step of glycolysis, which converts

1296
01:15:24.084 --> 01:15:27.543
phosphoenolpyruvate into pyruvate and generates ATP.

1297
01:15:29.064 --> 01:15:33.044
PKM gene gives rise to two different alternative splicing isoforms,

1298
01:15:33.144 --> 01:15:36.884
PKM1 and PKM2. So they both catalyze the very same

1299
01:15:36.924 --> 01:15:40.824
reaction. The only difference is that PKM1 is constitutively active,

1300
01:15:41.284 --> 01:15:45.264
instead PKM2 is less active, and it can be allosterically

1301
01:15:45.364 --> 01:15:49.024
regulated. And what we know so far is that cancer cells

1302
01:15:49.044 --> 01:15:52.694
preferentially express the M2 isoform, so the less active one,

1303
01:15:53.144 --> 01:15:56.924
because this gives them more flexibility and sustains tumor

1304
01:15:56.984 --> 01:16:00.564
growth. So given our data showing that pyruvate kinase was

1305
01:16:00.624 --> 01:16:04.364
upregulated upon loss of BRCA2, we wanted to dig in more

1306
01:16:04.424 --> 01:16:08.204
into the two different isoforms. And we were surprised to find

1307
01:16:08.264 --> 01:16:11.824
that the loss of BRCA2 induces the overexpression of the

1308
01:16:11.944 --> 01:16:14.824
M1 isoform rather than the expected M2.

1309
01:16:15.354 --> 01:16:19.144
And we found this in two different cell lines, the LD1 and ID8, at the

1310
01:16:19.244 --> 01:16:22.664
RNA level, at the protein level, and also if we look at the activity.

1311
01:16:23.404 --> 01:16:27.204
And this is in knockout models, so we wanted to see whether this could be

1312
01:16:27.244 --> 01:16:30.724
recapitulated also in a transient, acute model.

1313
01:16:31.024 --> 01:16:34.844
And also BRCA2 knockdown, just 48 hours of BRCA2 knockdown

1314
01:16:34.964 --> 01:16:38.944
was sufficient to upregulate M1 isoform in both cell lines

1315
01:16:38.984 --> 01:16:42.864
at RNA and protein level. And we could also see similar

1316
01:16:42.884 --> 01:16:46.624
results if we act on BRCA1. Also, if we do

1317
01:16:46.644 --> 01:16:49.764
knockdown of BRCA1 in the LD1, as well as

1318
01:16:50.224 --> 01:16:52.544
BRCA1 knockout clones in ID8.

1319
01:16:54.644 --> 01:16:58.074
And then we moved in vivo, and so we could see harvesting tumors from

1320
01:16:58.164 --> 01:17:00.224
tumor-bearing mice, we found the same results.

1321
01:17:00.304 --> 01:17:04.274
So M1 isoform was upregulated in BRCA2 knockout tumors,

1322
01:17:04.644 --> 01:17:08.584
but PKM2 was barely affected, and this happened at the protein

1323
01:17:08.664 --> 01:17:12.524
level measured by Western blot and immunochemistry, as well as if we look

1324
01:17:12.584 --> 01:17:16.544
at the activity, we can see the increase in activity is mainly due to

1325
01:17:16.704 --> 01:17:17.704
M1 isoform.

1326
01:17:19.304 --> 01:17:22.944
So then the next question is, okay, so loss of BRCA2 leads to this

1327
01:17:23.104 --> 01:17:27.024
high pyruvate kinase metabolic state, but can be thus

1328
01:17:27.164 --> 01:17:29.264
exploited as a metabolic vulnerability.

1329
01:17:29.784 --> 01:17:31.024
So as I mentioned before,

1330
01:17:32.244 --> 01:17:35.804
tumor cells or I would say most of tumor cells express

1331
01:17:35.904 --> 01:17:39.523
M2, the less active, which sustain tumor growth.

1332
01:17:40.124 --> 01:17:43.524
So this gave the rationale to develop PKM2

1333
01:17:43.604 --> 01:17:47.104
activators. So kind of mimicking or phenocopying a

1334
01:17:47.164 --> 01:17:48.674
constitutively active M1.

1335
01:17:49.724 --> 01:17:52.724
And different molecules have been developed, such as dasatinib,

1336
01:17:53.184 --> 01:17:54.884
TAP46, but they

1337
01:17:56.404 --> 01:18:00.374
didn't pass the preclinical stage because of lack of

1338
01:18:00.464 --> 01:18:04.444
efficacy in cancer context. So today we have mitapivat,

1339
01:18:04.524 --> 01:18:08.324
which is an FDA-approved PKM activator, which instead is used for

1340
01:18:08.344 --> 01:18:10.564
hemolytic anemia, so not in cancer.

1341
01:18:13.064 --> 01:18:16.804
However, these activators were tested in tumors, and they were not

1342
01:18:16.844 --> 01:18:20.684
effective enough, but the tumors have never been stratified according to their

1343
01:18:21.264 --> 01:18:24.304
BRCA mutational status, and this is what we wanted to do.

1344
01:18:24.964 --> 01:18:28.644
So we treated the cells with dasatinib, which is the PKM2

1345
01:18:28.704 --> 01:18:32.624
activator, and we could see that the activator selectively increased cell

1346
01:18:32.644 --> 01:18:36.004
death in BRCA2 knockouts tumor cells, not in the wild type.

1347
01:18:36.533 --> 01:18:39.994
And we can also see an upregulation of DNA damage markers, such as the

1348
01:18:40.084 --> 01:18:41.884
phosphorylation of gamma H2AX.

1349
01:18:44.064 --> 01:18:47.884
So then the question is, is this enhanced sensitivity

1350
01:18:47.894 --> 01:18:51.004
to the drug kind of correlated to

1351
01:18:51.364 --> 01:18:55.024
PKM1 upregulation? So to answer these questions, we

1352
01:18:55.084 --> 01:18:59.024
upregulated PKM1. We overexpressed PKM1 in BRCA2

1353
01:18:59.064 --> 01:19:01.524
wild type cells, as you can see here.

1354
01:19:01.564 --> 01:19:02.834
And we found that

1355
01:19:03.704 --> 01:19:07.204
PKM1 overexpression was sufficient to significantly enhance the

1356
01:19:07.224 --> 01:19:10.254
sensitivity to the activator in BRCA2 wild type cells,

1357
01:19:10.724 --> 01:19:14.404
suggesting that possibly this high pyruvate kinase activity state

1358
01:19:14.904 --> 01:19:18.784
mediated by PKM1 overexpression is at least in

1359
01:19:18.864 --> 01:19:22.844
part involved in this mechanism of sensitization

1360
01:19:22.904 --> 01:19:26.744
to the activator.And then we wanted to see whether

1361
01:19:26.784 --> 01:19:29.564
these findings could have some translational relevance

1362
01:19:30.924 --> 01:19:34.464
in vivo. And we used mitapivat, the FDA-approved drug,

1363
01:19:35.964 --> 01:19:39.744
in tumor-bearing mice. And we could see that mitapivat delayed tumor

1364
01:19:40.204 --> 01:19:43.834
growth selectively in BRCA knockout tumor cells, but not in the wild type.

1365
01:19:44.324 --> 01:19:48.244
And this treatment was also pretty safe since we saw that there was no changes

1366
01:19:48.284 --> 01:19:52.064
in body weight through the course of the experiment, as well as no

1367
01:19:52.104 --> 01:19:55.564
changes in weight of the target toxicity organs, liver and ovary.

1368
01:19:57.084 --> 01:20:00.884
So then the question was, why loss of BRCA2

1369
01:20:01.224 --> 01:20:03.764
leads to decreased sensitivity to PK activators.

1370
01:20:03.824 --> 01:20:06.104
What is the mechanism behind this?

1371
01:20:06.704 --> 01:20:10.624
And we could see that the activation of pyruvate kinase leads

1372
01:20:10.704 --> 01:20:14.364
to mitochondrial dysfunction, impacts mitochondria, and in fact,

1373
01:20:14.464 --> 01:20:14.744
by

1374
01:20:15.724 --> 01:20:19.444
doing tracing experiments using 13C glucose, we could

1375
01:20:19.564 --> 01:20:23.484
follow the fate of different glucose carbons, and we could see that the

1376
01:20:23.504 --> 01:20:27.444
drug, as well as the loss of BRCA2, leads to a decrease in

1377
01:20:27.504 --> 01:20:31.464
glucose oxidation measured by TCA cycle intermediates, malate,

1378
01:20:31.604 --> 01:20:34.704
and citrate. And this is consistent with also the

1379
01:20:34.724 --> 01:20:38.384
observation that there is a downregulation of the protein expression

1380
01:20:38.424 --> 01:20:41.004
level of the different complexes of the respiratory

1381
01:20:41.044 --> 01:20:44.324
chain. We also looked at PINK1,

1382
01:20:45.124 --> 01:20:48.654
which is a marker of mitochondrial quality and

1383
01:20:48.684 --> 01:20:52.404
mitophagy regulation. And what we found is that the activator in

1384
01:20:52.444 --> 01:20:56.224
BRCA2 wild-type cells causes a shift of PINK1 bands,

1385
01:20:56.264 --> 01:21:00.174
which indicates the autophosphorylation of PINK1, and so mitophagy

1386
01:21:00.404 --> 01:21:04.144
activation. Instead, what happens in BRCA2 knockout

1387
01:21:04.204 --> 01:21:08.184
cells with or without the drug, is that there is a downregulation of

1388
01:21:08.204 --> 01:21:11.384
PINK1 expression level, which may indicate

1389
01:21:12.444 --> 01:21:13.464
impairment of

1390
01:21:14.404 --> 01:21:17.644
mitophagy control. And this downregulation could be

1391
01:21:17.684 --> 01:21:21.224
phenocopied by overexpressing PKM1

1392
01:21:21.744 --> 01:21:25.564
in BRCA2 wild-type cell, as well as giving the product of the

1393
01:21:25.624 --> 01:21:27.244
reaction, which is pyruvate.

1394
01:21:28.204 --> 01:21:32.184
So given this data, in fact, showing that mitochondria are impacted,

1395
01:21:32.304 --> 01:21:35.824
we wanted to see whether mitochondria were going through some kind of

1396
01:21:35.864 --> 01:21:38.824
oxidative damage. And we found that

1397
01:21:40.324 --> 01:21:43.064
the drug, DAZ-508, the activator, causes

1398
01:21:43.264 --> 01:21:46.724
superoxide generation selectively in

1399
01:21:46.744 --> 01:21:50.644
mitochondria in both BRCA2 wild-type and BRCA2 knockout cells.

1400
01:21:51.064 --> 01:21:54.413
So then we wanted to see whether this oxidative stress in the

1401
01:21:54.464 --> 01:21:57.544
mitochondria may lead to impairment in mitophagy.

1402
01:21:58.004 --> 01:22:01.884
And so we looked at markers of mitophagy and autophagy, and we showed that

1403
01:22:01.924 --> 01:22:05.724
they were actually altered. In particular, the fact is stronger in

1404
01:22:05.744 --> 01:22:08.084
BRCA2 knockout cells with the drug.

1405
01:22:08.144 --> 01:22:11.784
And so it's showing that there is an impairment of the autophagic

1406
01:22:11.864 --> 01:22:15.724
flux. And this was also consistent with the fact that

1407
01:22:15.764 --> 01:22:19.644
we found an accumulation of multivesicular bodies measured

1408
01:22:19.684 --> 01:22:23.184
by EM selectively in BRCA knockout cells with the

1409
01:22:23.193 --> 01:22:23.804
activator.

1410
01:22:25.684 --> 01:22:29.384
Given these findings, we wanted to see whether this mitochondrial

1411
01:22:29.424 --> 01:22:33.164
oxidative stress was upstream and was the cause of all

1412
01:22:33.204 --> 01:22:37.034
these consequences. So we treated the cells with antioxidants,

1413
01:22:37.504 --> 01:22:41.184
and we could see that glutathione, and more effectively, the

1414
01:22:41.244 --> 01:22:45.164
superoxide dismutase mimetic, was able to reverse

1415
01:22:45.174 --> 01:22:49.004
the cell death induction caused by the drug in BRCA2 knockout

1416
01:22:49.084 --> 01:22:53.004
cells, suggesting that the oxidative stress, specifically in the mitochondria,

1417
01:22:53.324 --> 01:22:55.404
was the leading cause of this effect.

1418
01:22:56.604 --> 01:22:59.824
So to summarize, our working model is that

1419
01:22:59.944 --> 01:23:03.884
BRCA2-deficient cells grow in this highly active pyruvate

1420
01:23:03.924 --> 01:23:07.404
kinase state, which is mainly due to PKM1

1421
01:23:07.484 --> 01:23:11.164
expression. And if we further activate pyruvate

1422
01:23:11.224 --> 01:23:15.104
kinase with the activator, this leads to mitochondrial oxidative

1423
01:23:15.204 --> 01:23:18.944
stress and mitophagy and autophagy impairments leading to cell

1424
01:23:18.984 --> 01:23:19.304
death.

1425
01:23:20.684 --> 01:23:24.464
And with this, I want to thank my mentor, Marcos Goncalves, Luke

1426
01:23:24.474 --> 01:23:27.954
Cantley, all the members of the Goncalves Lab who helped me with the

1427
01:23:28.064 --> 01:23:31.084
project, all the collaborators, my funding sources.

1428
01:23:31.144 --> 01:23:34.664
I want to thank the American Italian Cancer Foundation and the Italian

1429
01:23:34.724 --> 01:23:38.284
Association for Cancer Research Fellowship, devoted in

1430
01:23:38.364 --> 01:23:41.924
memory of Francesca Barbieri. And thank you all for your attention.

1431
01:23:41.964 --> 01:23:43.163
Happy to take any questions.

1432
01:23:47.544 --> 01:23:50.574
Thank you. Any questions?

1433
01:23:53.144 --> 01:23:53.884
So great talk.

1434
01:23:54.284 --> 01:23:54.624
Thank you.

1435
01:23:55.384 --> 01:23:58.864
Thank you. So I was curious to know whether you also measured the cytoplasmic

1436
01:23:58.964 --> 01:24:00.964
levels of radical oxygen species.

1437
01:24:01.544 --> 01:24:05.304
And in addition to this, if you tried to combine the PK activator

1438
01:24:05.364 --> 01:24:09.324
with drugs that are known to be effective in BRCA deficient cells,

1439
01:24:09.364 --> 01:24:12.844
such as platinum compounds or PARP inhibitors, for instance. Thank you.

1440
01:24:12.864 --> 01:24:14.864
Yeah. Okay, thank you for your question.

1441
01:24:15.424 --> 01:24:19.084
So I didn't measure the oxidative stress in the cytoplasm, but

1442
01:24:19.144 --> 01:24:22.704
that's actually one thing that's next, is to compare that with

1443
01:24:22.724 --> 01:24:23.954
the mitochondrial.

1444
01:24:25.184 --> 01:24:28.664
So that we still don't know, but we will do that.

1445
01:24:28.724 --> 01:24:31.324
And for the second questions, we tried to combine

1446
01:24:32.024 --> 01:24:35.444
mitapivat with PARP inhibitors in vitro.

1447
01:24:35.944 --> 01:24:39.304
We observe an additive effect. We want to move in vivo,

1448
01:24:40.104 --> 01:24:43.684
and we are actually interested in seeing whether there is an additive

1449
01:24:43.744 --> 01:24:47.324
synergistic effect, and also if it has any

1450
01:24:47.364 --> 01:24:50.584
effect in the resistance appearance

1451
01:24:50.744 --> 01:24:54.604
or which is the effect of mitapivat in BRCA cells that are

1452
01:24:54.624 --> 01:24:58.184
already resistant to PARP. So we don't have the data yet,

1453
01:24:58.224 --> 01:25:01.644
but definitely wanted something what we wanted to do.

1454
01:25:02.044 --> 01:25:05.604
Thank you. You observed the increased DNA damage when you

1455
01:25:05.644 --> 01:25:06.524
combined the two-

1456
01:25:06.544 --> 01:25:06.724
Yeah

1457
01:25:07.304 --> 01:25:10.124
... courses? Okay, this could be potentially mediated also by an increased

1458
01:25:10.144 --> 01:25:11.904
accumulation of ROS, for instance?

1459
01:25:13.684 --> 01:25:17.464
Yeah. So we hypothesized that that's the damage that we

1460
01:25:17.524 --> 01:25:20.824
